Early forms, with complex vertebrae consisting of a number of separate elements, were placed in the suborder Rachitomi, and large Triassic aquatic forms with simpler vertebrae were placed in the suborder Stereospondyli. The basic rhachitomous condition is found in many primitive tetrapods, and is not unique to one group of temnospondyls.
